\begin_layout Subsection
Notice of Meetings
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The President, the Secretary, or the Board shall cause to be delivered to
 each member entitled to notice of the meeting, either personally, by mail,
 by fascimile transmission or by electronic transmission, not less than
 ten nor more than fifty days before the meeting, written notice stating
 the place, date and time of the meeting and, in the case of a special meeting,
 the purpose or purposes for which the meeting is called.
 If such notice is mailed, it shall be deemed delivered when deposited in
 the official government mail properly addressed to the member at their
 address as it appears on the records of the corporation with postage thereon
 prepaid.
 Notice provided in an electronic transmission is effective when it: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
is electronically transmitted to an address, location, or system designated
 by the recipient for that purpose, and is made pursuant to the consent
 provided by the recipient; or 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
has been posted on an electronic network along with a notification in the
 electronic network directed at the recipient, with failure of the notification
 delivery only being possible by opting out via the recipient.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Waiver of Notice
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whenever any notice is required to be given to any member under the provisions
 of these Bylaws, the Articles of Incorporation or applicable Washington
 law, a waiver thereof in writing, signed by the person or persons entitled
 to such notice, whether before or after the time stated therein, shall
 be deemed equivalent to the giving of such notice.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Meetings by Telephone
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Members of the corporation may participate in a meeting of members by means
 of a conference telephone or similar electronic communications equipment
 by means of which all persons participating in the meeting can hear each
 other at the same time.
 Participation by such means shall constitute presence in person at a meeting.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Members' Dues, Fees, and Assessments
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Each member must pay, within the time and on the conditions set by the board,
 the dues, fees, and assessments in amounts to be fixed from time to time
 by the board.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Members in Good Standing
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Members who have paid the required dues, fees, and assessments in accordance
 with these bylaws and who are not suspended shall be members in good standing.
 
\end_layout

