\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Vacancies
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The board of directors may fill vacancies, via the affirmative vote of a
 majority of the remaining directors despite less than a quorum of directors
 remain on the board, due to the expiration of a directors term of office,
 resignation, death, or removal of a director or may appoint new directors
 to fill a previously unfilled position, subject to the maximum number of
 directors under these bylaws.
 A Director who fills a vacancy shall serve for the balance of the term
 of the director being replaced.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Unexpected Vacancies
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Vacancies due to resignation, death, or removal shall be filled by the board
 members for the balance of the term of the director being replaced.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Resignation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Any Director may resign at any time by delivering written notice to the
 President or the Secretary at the registered office of the Corporation,
 or by giving oral or written notice at any meeting of the Directors.
 Any such resignation shall take effect at the time specified therein, or
 if the time is not specified, upon delivery thereof and, unless otherwise
 specified therein, the acceptance of such resignation shall not be necessary
 to make it effective.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Removal
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A director may be removed by two-thirds vote of directors then in office,
 if: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
At a meeting of the Board, one or more Directors may be removed from office,
 with or without cause, by two-thirds of the votes cast by Directors then
 in office.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A director may be removed by confirmation of the President without a vote,
 if:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The director is absent and unexcused from two or more board meetings in
 a twelve month period.
 The president is empowered to excuse directors from attendance for a reason
 deemed adequate by the president.
 The president shall not have the power to excuse themself from the board
 meeting attendance and in that case, the secretary shall excuse the president.
 If the secretary and the president are absent, the absence may be counted
 as unexcused for both but not only one of the absentees by a two-thirds
 vote of directors then in office.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A director may be removed by confirmation of the Secretary without a vote,
 if:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The director is the president and is absent and unexcused from two or more
 board meetings in a twelve month period.
 The secretary is empowered to excuse the president from attendance for
 a reason deemed adequate by the secretary.
 If the secretary and the president are absent, the absence may be counted
 as unexcused for both but not only one of the absentees by a two-thirds
 vote of directors then in office.
\end_layout

