\begin_layout Subsection
Election and Term of Office
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The officers of the Corporation shall be elected each year by the Board
 at the annual meeting of the Board.
 Unless an officer dies, resigns, or is removed from office, he or she shall
 hold office until the next annual meeting of the Board or until their successor
 is elected.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Resignation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Any officer may resign at any time by delivering written notice to the President
, the Secretary or the Board, or by giving oral or written notice at any
 meeting of the Board.
 Any such resignation shall take effect at the time specified therein, or
 if the time is not specified, upon delivery thereof and, unless otherwise
 specified therein, the acceptance of such resignation shall not be necessary
 to make it effective.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Removal
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Any officer or agent elected or appointed by the Board may be removed from
 office by the Board whenever in its judgment the best interests of the
 Corporation would be served thereby, but such removal shall be without
 prejudice to the contract rights, if any, of the person so removed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Vacancies
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A vacancy in any office created by the death, resignation, removal, disqualifica
tion, creation of a new office or any other cause may be filled by the Board
 for the unexpired portion of the term or for a new term established by
 the Board.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
President
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The President shall, subject to the Board’s control, supervise and control
 all of the assets, business and affairs of the Corporation.
 The President shall preside over meetings of the Board.
 The President may sign deeds, mortgages, bonds, contracts, or other instruments
, except when the signing and execution thereof have been expressly delegated
 by the Board or by these Bylaws to some other officer or agent of the Corporati
on or are required by law to be otherwise signed or executed by some other
 officer or in some other manner.
 In general, the President shall perform all duties incident to the office
 of President and such other duties as are assigned to the President by
 the Board from time to time.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Vice President
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the event of the death of the President or their inability to act, the
 Vice President (or if there is more than one Vice President, the Vice President
 who was designated by the Board as the successor to the President, or if
 no Vice President is so designated, the Vice President whose name first
 appears in the Board resolution electing officers) shall perform the duties
 of the President, except as may be limited by resolution of the Board,
 with all the powers of and subject to all the restrictions upon the President.
 Vice Presidents shall have, to the extent authorized by the President or
 the Board, the same powers as the President to sign deeds, mortgages, bonds,
 contracts or other instruments.
 Vice Presidents shall perform such other duties as from time to time may
 be assigned to them by the President or the Board.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Secretary
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Secretary shall: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
keep or cause to be kept the minutes of meetings of the Board, and minutes
 which may be maintained by committees of the Board; 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
see that all notices are duly given in accordance with the provisions of
 these Bylaws or as required by law; 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
be custodian or ensure the safe custody of the corporate records of the
 Corporation; 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
keep records of the post office and email address of each Director and each
 officer; and 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
in general perform all duties incident to the office of Secretary and such
 other duties as from time to time may be assigned to the Secretary by the
 President or the Board.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Treasurer
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If requested by the Board, the Treasurer shall give a bond for the faithful
 discharge of their duties in such amount and with such surety or sureties
 as the Board may determine.
 The Treasurer shall have charge and custody of and be responsible for oversight
 of all funds and securities of the Corporation; receive and give receipts
 for moneys due and payable to the Corporation from any source whatsoever,
 and ensure the deposit all such moneys in the name of the Corporation in
 banks, trust companies or other depositories selected in accordance with
 the provisions of these Bylaws; provide financial reports to the Board
 at its meetings and on request and in general perform all of the duties
 incident to the office of Treasurer and such other duties as from time
 to time may be assigned to them by the President or the Board
\end_layout

